In his 1992 essay, Popper analyzed the fall of the Soviet system:

Internal Collapse: The system failed because of its own internal contradictions and the rigidity of its ideology, not just external pressure.

Ideological Poverty: @@The Marxist-Leninist dogma prevented the system from adapting to reality or learning from mistakes.@@

''Error Correction: Because the system suppressed criticism, it could not correct its own errors, leading to systemic stagnation.''

Moral Victory of the Open Society: The collapse proved that societies that allow for free discussion and "conjecture and refutation" are more resilient than those that don't.